# Vite & Vitest Guidelines

## Vite Configuration
- Maintain single vite.config.ts at project root
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Define path aliases for clean imports
- Optimize build settings for production
- Include plugins in logical order

## Vitest Setup
- Configure vitest in vite.config.ts or separate vitest.config.ts
- Use testing-library/react for component tests
- Implement setup files for common test configurations
- Utilize mocks for external dependencies

## Test Structure
- Co-locate test files with source code
- Name test files with .test.ts or .test.tsx suffix
- Group related tests in describe blocks
- Use clear test descriptions
- Follow AAA pattern (Arrange-Act-Assert)

## Test Coverage
- Aim for 80%+ coverage on components
- Test component rendering and interactions
- Test custom hooks with renderHook
- Test utility functions with unit tests
- Include edge cases and error states